Alfred buys an old scooter for Rs. X and spends Rs. Y on its repairs. If he sells the scooter for Rs. Z (Z>X+Y). 
Write a program to help Alfred to find his gain percent. Get all the above-mentioned values through the keyboard and find the gain percent.

Program:

x = int(input())
y = int(input())
z = int(input())
print(f"{((z - (x + y)) / (x + y) ) * 100:.2f} is the gain percent.")
